# Integration System Architecture & Permissions

## 🎯 CORE PRINCIPLES

**Every integration must be secure, intuitive, and provide granular business owner control over employee access.**

### Integration System Philosophy
1. **Zero Trust Architecture**: Never trust, always verify - continuous authentication and authorization
2. **Principle of Least Privilege**: Users get minimum access needed for their role
3. **Business Owner Control**: Comprehensive permission management for business owners
4. **Intuitive Design**: Clean, consistent UI/UX across all integrations
5. **Audit Trail**: Complete logging of all permission changes and access

## 🏗️ Integration Structure Standards

### Required Integration Architecture
```typescript
// REQUIRED: Every integration must follow this structure
interface Integration {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
  category: IntegrationCategory;
  
  // Core Configuration
  config: {
    enabled: boolean;
    defaultEnabled: boolean; // New integrations default to true
    apiEndpoint: string;
    version: string;
    lastSync: Date;
  };
  
  // Permission System
  permissions: IntegrationPermissions;
  
  // UI Configuration
  ui: {
    icon: string;
    color: string;
    headerVisible: boolean; // Show in header by default
    position: number; // Header order
  };
  
  // Business Logic
  handlers: {
    onEnable: () => Promise<void>;
    onDisable: () => Promise<void>;
    onPermissionChange: (permissions: PermissionChange[]) => Promise<void>;
  };
}
```

